     One day, I chanced to meet Thoran as I was once more heading from the center of Antonica to return to Kelethin. He had just joined a new guild, Victus Fortis, and seemed extraordinarily happy. This assorted group of Norrathians from all walks of life were, it seemed, united in the joy all took in assisting others and facing the challenges of good versus evil in the land, dedicating themselves to the &quot;brave way of life&quot; their name indicated. Thoran spoke of them as fondly and affectionately as if they were family, and informed me that he had recommended both me and my sister Raynn to them as recruits.<br>
     I was overwhelmed. Up to this point, I had not seriously considered joining a guild, although of course Blakeley and I had over the seasons dreamed of one that would match our ideals. But Thoran's words struck a deep chord within me, and meeting by chance an officer named Ronstad one night, I spoke to this brave warrior regarding Victus to see if they were indeed such like-minded souls as would appeal to me. He greeted my approach so warmly, having already heard of me from Thoran, that again I was near overwhelmed. So when I came the next day to Freeport, and came across Raynn's friend Wegian, who also strongly urged me to join Victus Fortis, and knowing him to be a sterling and staunch individual, I accepted the invitation he gave me. I was then in my 23rd season….<br>
     Tuilere, dear, I cannot begin to tell you how belonging to Victus changed my life and made it once more meaningful. Several of the boon fighting companions of my earlier days were already members, to my joy, and as the days passed I met many more who quickly became true friends and as close as brothers or sisters to me. With renewed courage and energy I set forth once more to face the challenges of the world's evil minions and defeat them, and we have had many a merry adventure together. In turn I considered each of my friends and acquaintances and from them approached those most like unto my guildmates and urged them also to join VF, and thus brought Blakeley, Armonico and Tisharmo into the guild as well. But though I looked long and hard for her, I could not find my sister Raynn.<br>
     When we were in our teens, Raynn came upon a human child, Lorelin, in the midst of the carnage of an orc attack in the Commons. The child's parents, indeed the entire settlement, had been wiped out in the attack, leaving Lorelin the only survivor. Not knowing what else to do with her, Raynn took Lorelin into her charge and across the ocean to Kelethin, adopting her into our family and serving as both mother and sister to the young bard. This worked quite well for all concerned, but over the seasons the girl became increasingly curious about her roots and longed to learn of her natural family as well. One day she received a letter from an aunt in Qeynos and decided to undertake the long journey to visit her and perhaps learn more of her departed parents. Raynn, having no training to undertake at the time and wanting a vacation, and of course desiring to look after the child, set off with her one day from the docks near Kaladim to take ship for Freeport on the first stage, and that was the last any of us heard from either for a long, long time. As I was during this time overly preoccupied with my own affairs, it did not occur to me to worry. But now, failing to trace their movements beyond taking ship on the Ocean of Tears, I grew increasingly concerned and was compelled to send a note to Kemie in case she knew more. Alas, she was as much in the dark as I was about the whereabouts of our sisters or their welfare! They seemed to have vanished from the face of Norrath, as if they had never been….<br>
